<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1801,2006]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,401,1873,1898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bender" box="[407,673,1873,1898]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" refString="Bender, R. &amp; Dierl, W. (1982) Zur Kenntnis der Lepidoptera Sumatras. Eine neue Art der Gattung Streblote Hubner, [1820] 1816 (Lepidoptera, Lasiocampidae). Entomofauna, 3 (23), 367 - 370." type="journal article" year="1982">Bender and Dierl (1982)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[790,1026,1873,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Lasiocampidae" genus="Streblote" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lajonquierei">
<emphasis box="[790,1026,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Streblote lajonquierei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sumatra, with the illustration of male genitalia and 8th sternite. This species was later synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1200,1909,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Lasiocampidae" genus="Alompra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ferruginea" subSpecies="bidiensis">
<emphasis box="[950,1200,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">A. ferruginea bidiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[1241,1432,1909,1934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1987) The Moths of Borneo, Part 3. Superfamily Bombycoidea: Families Lasiocampidae, Eupterotidae, Bombycidae, Brahmaeidae, Saturniidae, Sphingidae. Southdene, Kuala Lumpur, 199 pp." type="book" year="1987">Holloway (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Both Bornean and Sumatran specimens (illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bender" box="[769,1035,1945,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" refString="Bender, R. &amp; Dierl, W. (1982) Zur Kenntnis der Lepidoptera Sumatras. Eine neue Art der Gattung Streblote Hubner, [1820] 1816 (Lepidoptera, Lasiocampidae). Entomofauna, 3 (23), 367 - 370." type="journal article" year="1982">Bender and Dierl, 1982</bibRefCitation>
) are identical in male genitalia and shape of the 8th abdominal sternite, thus we regard the two populations belong to the same species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
See the diagnosis part of 
<taxonomicName box="[610,759,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Lasiocampidae" genus="Alompra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis box="[610,759,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">A. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for details. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Distribution.</emphasis>
Borneo and Sumatra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Hitherto only three specimens were known, the Sumatra adults occur in the lower mountain range in mid August (
<bibRefCitation author="Bender" box="[326,594,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="155" refString="Bender, R. &amp; Dierl, W. (1982) Zur Kenntnis der Lepidoptera Sumatras. Eine neue Art der Gattung Streblote Hubner, [1820] 1816 (Lepidoptera, Lasiocampidae). Entomofauna, 3 (23), 367 - 370." type="journal article" year="1982">Bender and Dierl, 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
